SIMPLE: reputable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reputable
<hw>Rep"u*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(r?p"?-t?-b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Repute</er>.]</ety> <def>Having, or worthy of, good repute; held in
esteem; honorable; praiseworthy; <as>as, a <ex>reputable</ex> man or
character; <ex>reputable</ex> conduct.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the article of danger, it is as <qex>reputable</qex> to elude
an enemy as defeat one.</q> <rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Respectable; creditable; estimable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rep"u ta*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Rep"u*ta*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reputation</ent>⟦br⟧
